<h2>JavaScript Classes are not hoisted</h2>

<p>You will get an error if you try to use a class before it is declared.</p>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
//You cannot use the class yet.
//mycar = new Car("Ford")
//This would raise an error.

class Car {
  constructor(brand) {
    this.carname = brand;
  }
}

//Now you can use the class:
mycar = new Car("Ford")
</script>

</body>
</html>
